 <hr>
 <h2 id="head-1c659c68d6612e69e054750a0fabba8811b9ae96">Finding and recognizing Narsil</h2>
There is no one likely location that Narsil can be found in. <p>
To help you recognize Narsil if you find it:  
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Destroy (or ID) every broken sword you find. If you happen across one that cannot be destroyed, <em>keep it!</em>, for you may have found the famed Narsil.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Alternatively, you can check the damage dice of every broken sword you find. Narsil has 3d2 damage, whereas normal broken swords only have 1d2.  
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
However, you <em>must</em> ID Narsil in order to receive the quest to have it be reforged. 
</p>
<h2 id="head-f04f6c484cb8e4f6135175aacd0811c45cd9ba9c">Reforging Narsil</h2>
If it really is Narsil, take it to Aragorn in Minas Anor. He will reforge it into Anduril and then give it to you as a reward. <h2 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h2>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I'm not sure whether Aragorn will accept Narsil if it is unidentified. Never tried it. <p>
<strong><a href="./ErisDiscordia">ErisDiscordia</a></strong>: I found Narsil recently and got a special ("yellow") message very shortly after finding it. Is that only upon ID'ing it? Either way, that should probably be mentioned here. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I don't remember -- I've only found Narsil once and that was a while ago. Ummm.../me looks cross-eyed at the code... q_narsil.c only has Aragorn's speech in it, not the blurb when you first find it, and I don't know where else to look. 
</p>
<p>
BTW, is it just me, or could Aragorn's speech be reworked a little?? <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
Anyway, I agree with you. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: As for most quests, the code is in q_foo.c and the quest text in tables.c: 
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: (me the one-day-old non-veteran of diving ToME code: Gee, that's logical! <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile4.png" alt=";)" height="15" width="15"> <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/biggrin.png" alt=":D" height="15" width="15"> Thanks for telling me though.) 
    </ul>


<p>
<em>You have found Narsil, a broken sword. It is said that the sword that was broken shall be reforged... Maybe it is this one. You should bring it to Aragorn at Minas Anor -- he would know.</em> 
</p>
<p>
Looking at the code, you can only return Narsil to Aragon if the quest was taken, i.e. if Narsil was identified. 
</p>
